messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Yes, I'd like to report a shooting, please.
Okay, what is the address?
The address is 9063 C Lane, S-E-A, Lane, Southwest.
Okay, so it's not happening at your residence?
No, it's right next door. The lady that lives there, her husband just came in and said that she shot herself.
Okay, I understand. So, her husband found her like that?
Yes, he said she shot herself.
Alright, and you said the address is 9063 C Lane?
Yes, I think so. I'm not exactly sure of the address.
Okay, I came to drop, you all.
I walked into the house. I heard two loud shots and then she's... Oh, my God.
Okay, calm down. Is someone there with you?
Yes, the neighbor's here.
Alright, can you talk to them instead?
No, she's gone. My God, she's gone.
Okay, how old is she?
Oh my God. Oh my God. Oh my God.
Stay calm, okay? You said she's gone?
Yes, right through the center of the chest.
So, the shot is in the chest?
Yes, right through the center.
And you heard the shots when you walked in?
No, I was outside. She told me to watch Katie outside on the scooter.
Do you want to stay on the phone until help arrives?
Sure, if you do.
Alright, medic 16 is on the way.
Okay.
If you think of anything else, just let me know, okay? Where's the gun at now?
I have no idea.
Okay. Are you inside the residence?
No, I'm outside.
Alright, you're outside. Did you go in there right after you heard the shots?
Yes, I ran in and saw her laying on the floor. I put Katie out of the house because I didn't want her to see.
Right. How old is Katie?
She's four.
I understand. They just want to make sure the gun is put away because it's a crime scene. Can you find her pager or cell phone?
I'll look for it, okay?
Do you have your cell phone on you?
Yes, ma'am.
Alright, law enforcement is on the way. Do you want to hang up?
Sure, okay. Bye.
Bye, thank you.
